Key Match Events: Jaren Jackson Jr. recorded a triple-double with 35 points, 13 rebounds, and 5 assists
Memphis won for the 10th time in the last 11 home games
Pre-Game Insights: Both teams were without their starting backcourts due to injuries
Dallas was missing its top two scorers and 52.4 points a game due to Luka Doncic and Kyrie Irving being out with injuries
Post-Match Reflections: Memphis got in an early deficit with turnovers and poor shooting, but righted things with better control of the offense through the final three quarters
